# RPG Class and Ability Schema

This document outlines the JSON schema used in `data/classes.json` to define character classes, their stat growths, and their combat abilities. It is specifically tailored to show what the `action-handler.js` currently supports.

---

## 1. Class Object Structure
Each class defines the core combat identity and stat affinities for a character.

```json
{
  "id": "spirit_incinerator",
  "name": "Spirit Incinerator",
  "icon": "🔥",
  "element": "fire",          // Base elemental affinity (used for STAB calculations)
  "tag": "Fire / Life Force", // Sub-description tag 
  "description": "Flavor text...",
  "color": "#c03010",         // Hex color used for UI themes
  "role": "Warrior",          // Abstract role designation
  "stat_multipliers": {       // Multiplies the character's base_stats
    "hp": 0.85, "mp": 1.0, "atk": 1.5, "def": 0.7, "spd": 1.15, "mag": 1.1
  },
  "growthPerLevel": {         // Flat stat additions on level up
    "hp": 6, "mp": 5, "atk": 3, "def": 2, "spd": 5, "mag": 3 
  },
  "abilities": [ ... ]        // Array of Ability Objects
}
```

---

## 2. Ability Object Structure

Each ability represents an action the character can take in combat.

```json
{
  "id": "paramita_papilio",
  "name": "Paramita Papilio",
  "icon": "🦋",
  "mp": 6,                    // MP cost
  "type": "buff",             // Determines the combat logic branch (see Types below)
  "description": "Enter the butterfly state...",
  "isUltimate": true,         // (Optional) Sets this as an ultimate skill (cinematic delay)
  "effect": { ... }           // The payload interpreted by action-handler.js
}
```

### Ability Types (`type`)
The `type` key dictates which branch of logic in `action-handler.js` will process the move.
*   `"physical"`: Standard attack scaling off ATK.
*   `"magic_damage"`: Spell casting scaling off MAG.
*   `"heal"`: Restores party HP.
*   `"buff"`: Applies positive stat modifiers to the caster or party.
*   `"debuff"`: Applies negative stat modifiers to the enemy.
*   `"regen"`: Sets a heal-over-time effect on the party.
*   `"stun"`: Attempts to skip the enemy's next turn.
*   `"steal"`: Attempts to acquire gold/items.
*   `"run"`: Attempts to flee the battle.

---

## 3. Effect Payload Schema (`effect`)

The `effect` object is highly modular. You can mix and match properties based on the `type`.

### Damage Modifiers (`physical` / `magic_damage`)
*   `"dmgMultiplier": 1.5` — Base damage scalar.
*   `"element": "ice"` — Overrides the attack element for this specific move.
*   `"aoe": true` — If true, the attack hits all active enemies.
*   `"statScale": "spd"` — Adds bonus flat damage scaling linearly with a specific stat (e.g., `spd`, `def`, `hp`, `maxHp`).
*   `"lowHpDmgBonus": 0.5` — Damage increases as the caster's HP shrinks.
*   `"lifeSteal": 0.15` — Heals the caster or party for X% of the damage dealt.
*   `"hpCostPercent": 0.3` — Sacrifices X% of the caster's *current* HP to initiate the attack.

### Healing Modifiers (`heal` / `regen`)
*   `"healBase": 40` & `"healRandom": 20` — Base healing formula (40 + up to 20 variance).
*   `"healPercent": 0.5` — Heals a strict percentage of the target's Max HP.
*   `"cleanse": true` — Clears `stunned`, `frozen`, and `debuff` statuses from targets.

### Primary Buffing & Debuffing (`buff` / `debuff`)
*To ensure a buff/debuff expires properly, it must declare a primary `stat`.*
*   `"stat": "atk"` — The specific stat to alter (`def`, `atk`, `mag`, `spd`).
*   `"multiplier": 1.5` — Amplifies the primary target stat by X%. (Use `< 1.0` for debuffs).
*   `"duration": 3` — Number of turns before the buff/debuff expires and resets.

### Secondary Buff Modifiers (Can be stacked on Buffs)
*   `"damageReduction": 0.25` — Target takes 25% less raw damage from all sources while active.
*   `"reflect": 0.15` — 15% of damage received is dealt back to the attacker.
*   `"evasion": 0.3` — 30% chance to flatly dodge incoming physical attacks.
*   `"hpRegenAmt": 25` — Flat HP restored at the end of each turn.
*   `"guardMark": true` — Taunt; forces enemies to target this character exclusively.
*   `"guardian": true` — Spawns the "Phantom Guardian" shield for 2 turns.
*   `"fireAmp": 1.33` — Amplifies all outgoing fire damage.
*   `"absorb": "fire"` — Incoming damage of this element heals the character instead.
*   `"summonBoost": 1.3` — Special multiplier applied solely to "Summon" abilities.

### Status Inflictions
*   `"slowChance": 0.4` — (Usually tied to Ice) 40% chance to temporarily reduce enemy SPD.
*   `"freezeChance": 0.6` — 60% chance to set `enemy.frozen = true` (skips turn).
*   `"stunChance": 0.5` — 50% chance to set `enemy.stunned = true` (skips turn).
